    "plan_content": "Here's the plan I've put together after exploring the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### What I found\n\n- **Exact pattern to follow**: `packages/next/server.js` / `server.d.ts` / `user-agent.ts` — I'll replicate the same dual-export JS pattern, re-export `.d.ts` pattern, and interface+functions TypeScript pattern.\n- **Test framework**: Jest — same as `adapters/headers.test.ts` in the same `spec-extension/` directory (using `describe`/`it`/`expect`).\n- **Zero existing geo header parsing** — net-new code, no risk of breaking anything. There are only stub comments/`undefined` returns for `geo` in `next-request.ts` and `app-route/module.ts`, which are untouched.\n- **`package.json` insertion point**: after `\"form.js\"` / `\"form.d.ts\"` (since `g` follows `f` alphabetically).\n\n---\n\n### Files to create/modify\n\n| Action | Path |\n|--------|------|\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.js` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` |\n| **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` |\n| **Edit** | `packages/next/package.json` (`files` array only) |\n\n---\n\n### Key implementation decisions\n\n- **`null` → `undefined` normalisation**: `headers.get()` returns `null` for missing headers; `?? undefined` converts to `undefined` so `Geo` fields are `string | undefined`, not `string | null` — required for strict mode.\n- **Header priority**: Vercel (`x-vercel-ip-country`) takes precedence over Cloudflare (`cf-ipcountry`) for `countryCode`.\n- **`country` name**: derived from `COUNTRY_NAMES` lookup map (10 entries); unknown codes yield `undefined`.\n- **Haversine**: uses `Math.atan2` (numerically stable), returns km.\n- **Zero external dependencies** in `geo.ts` — no `next/dist/compiled/` imports needed.\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types                          # TypeScript check (~10s)\npnpm test-unit --testPathPattern=geo.test         # Jest unit tests\npnpm --filter=next build && node -e \"require('./packages/next/geo')\"  # smoke test\n```",
